Born in T.O. finished High School in East York and went off to Kingston for a few years. Left there to make sure Tweed was suitable for Elvis to live in. After that I found Trenton to my liking and have been here since '77.

We had an ice shack out there too.  Lake Wattapahna.  We had a little wood-burner tin box stove that would glow red hot when it really got going.  You couldn't sit near it.  We'd be down to our t-shirts while it's minus 30's outside.  I haven't been back there since we left in 1970 but I've seen some pics and it looks like pretty much everything is gone but a few of the hangers and maybe the steam plant.  Apparently though, the town of Rivers survived the base closing and is doing fairly well.
